DataElement.preferredName: Recombinant Granulocyte Colony-Stimulating Factor Administered Checkbox Ind
DataElement.preferredDefinition: Indicator determining whether or not (G-CSF) was administered.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: A recombinant therapeutic agent which is chemically identical to or similar to the endogenous cytokine granulocyte colony-stimulating factor (G-CSF).  Secreted by monocytes, macrophages and neutrophils and other cells after activation, G-CSF stimulates the proliferation and differentiation of hematopoietic progenitor cells committed to the neutrophil/ granulocyte lineage. (NCI04)_The act of having given something (e.g., a medication or test).

ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: G-CSF. A colony-stimulating factor that stimulates the production of neutrophils (a type of white blood cell).  It is a cytokine that belongs to the family of drugs called hematopoietic (blood-forming) agents. Also called filgrastim.

Concepts.definition: A recombinant therapeutic agent which is chemically identical to or similar to the endogenous cytokine granulocyte colony-stimulating factor (G-CSF). (NCI04)
The act of having given something (e.g., a medication or test).
